	<section class="content-section">
		<h2>Comprehensive Implant Services</h2>
		<p>We provide start-to-finish implant care under one roof, ensuring consistent quality and a comfortable patient experience.</p>
		<ul>
			<li><strong>Single Tooth Implants:</strong> The ideal way to replace a single missing tooth. Unlike a traditional dental bridge, an implant does not require filing down the healthy adjacent teeth, preserving your natural tooth structure.</li>
			<li><strong>Implant-Supported Bridges & Dentures:</strong> For patients missing multiple teeth, a few strategically placed implants can securely anchor a bridge or a full denture, eliminating the slipping and discomfort associated with traditional removable dentures.</li>
			<li><strong>Guided Bone Regeneration (GBR) / Bone Grafting:</strong> If you have been missing a tooth for a while, your jawbone may have receded. We offer bone grafting procedures to rebuild bone density, creating a strong, stable foundation for your future implant.</li>
			<li><strong>Sinus Lifts:</strong> When placing implants in the upper back jaw, there may not be enough bone height below the sinus cavity. A sinus lift safely raises the sinus floor to allow for successful implant placement.</li>
		</ul>
	</section>

	<section class="content-section">
		<h2>Why We Trust Straumann BLX</h2>
		<p>Not all dental implants are created equal. We proudly use the Swiss-engineered <a href="https://www.straumann.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Straumann implant system</a>, specifically the BLX line. Straumann is a global leader in implant dentistry, known for its exceptional clinical research, high success rates, and innovative surface technologies that promote faster, stronger integration with your jawbone.</p>
	</section>

	<section class="content-section">
		<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
		<div class="faq">
			<details>
				<summary>Does getting a dental implant hurt?</summary>
				<p>Most patients are surprised by how little discomfort is involved. The procedure is performed under local anesthesia, so you will not feel pain during the surgery. Post-operative discomfort is typically mild and easily managed with over-the-counter pain relievers.</p>
			</details>
			<details>
				<summary>How long does the dental implant process take?</summary>
				<p>The entire process usually takes several months. After the implant post is placed in the jawbone, it needs time (typically 3-6 months) to fuse with the bone (osseointegration). Once healed, the custom crown is attached. If bone grafting is required, the timeline may be extended.</p>
			</details>
			<details>
				<summary>How much do dental implants cost in Surrey?</summary>
				<p>The cost varies based on several factors, including the number of implants needed, whether bone grafting or sinus lifts are required, and the type of final restoration. During your initial consultation, we will provide a comprehensive, transparent treatment plan with exact costs.</p>
			</details>
			<details>
				<summary>Are dental implants covered by CDCP or private insurance?</summary>
				<p>Typically, complex restorative work like dental implants is considered a major service and is not covered by the CDCP. Private dental insurance policies vary; some may cover a portion of the crown or the extraction. We offer flexible financing options to make this life-changing investment more affordable.</p>
			</details>
		</div>
	</section>

